  "texts": [
    "Recall that K is absolutely convex if K is convex and whenever x ∈ K, then also -x ∈ K. Given a Banach space Y, u ∈ Y and ρ ∈ Y *, we use the interchangeable notation⟨ρ, u⟩ = u(ρ) = ρ(u).",
    "Proposition 4.2.",
    "Suppose Y is a Banach space and K ⊂ Y * is absolutely convex.",
    "Suppose A ⊂ Y * is weak * open, convex, ρ ∈ A an A ∩ K = ∅.",
    "Then there exists u ∈ Y such that u(ρ) > sup k∈K |u(k)|.Proof."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}